    "content": "nullSalesforce B2B Commerce for Visualforce\nTABLE OF CONTENTS\nClose\nClose\nSearch\nSearch\n Salesforce B2B Commerce for Visualforce\n Get Started with B2B Commerce for Visualforce\n Manage Storefront Details and Metadata\n Set Up Product Data for B2B Commerce for Visualforce\n Help Buyers Discover Products on Your Storefront\n Price and Sell Products for B2B Commerce for Visualforce\n Support Buyer Accounts for B2B Commerce for Visualforce\n Provide a Smooth Path to Purchase for Storefront Buyers\n Customize the Storefront User Experience\n Considerations for Storefront User Experience Customizations\n Configure the Default Storefront Pages\n Home Page\n Checkout Page\n My Account Page\n Product Compare Page\n Product Detail Page\n Configure Product Info and Options on the Product Detail Page\n Guidelines for Creating Page Sections\n Show a Product's Long Description on the Product Detail Page\n Show Related Products on the Product Detail Page\n Show Product Specs on the Product Detail Page\n Make Documentation Available on the Product Detail Page\n Show Custom Document Types on the Product Detail Page\n Show Shipping Information on the Product Detail Page\n Show Custom Content on the Product Detail Page\n Product List Page\n Scaled Cart Page\n Shopping Cart Page\n Site Login Page\n Site Register Page\n Modify the Column Layout of a Storefront Page\n Add Widgets to Storefront Pages with Visualforce Components\n Customize Storefront Headings and Text with Page Labels\n Provide Intuitive Storefront Navigation with Menus\n Author Custom Content for a Storefront Page\n Style Your Storefront with a Theme\n Extend the Default Storefront Pages\n Source Options for Storefront Media\n Allow Only One Country, Territory, or State in Address Picklists\n Strategize for Storefront Success\n Deliver Storefront Performance and Security\n Market Templates for B2B Commerce for Visualforce\n Solution Resources for B2B Commerce for Visualforce\n\nYou are here:\n\nSALESFORCE HELP\nDOCS\nVISUALFORCE B2B COMMERCE\nProduct Detail Page\n\nThe Product Detail page shows pricing, catalog, inventory, and descriptive information for a specific product. You can configure which details you want to show, and which options are available for ordering the product.\n\nREQUIRED EDITIONS\n\nSalesforce Compatibility\n\nSalesforce Classic (not available in all orgs) and Lightning Experience for Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer editions.\n\n\n\n\nB2B Commerce Compatibility\n\nB2B Commerce for Visualforce Winter ’21 (version 4.13)\nB2B Commerce for Visualforce Spring ’20 (version 4.12)\nB2B Commerce for Visualforce Summer ’19 (version 4.11)\nB2B Commerce for Visualforce Spring ’19 (version 4.10)\nB2B Commerce for Visualforce Summer ’18 (version 4.9)\nUSER EXPERIENCE COMPATIBILITY\nInterface\tBootstrap 3 or classic\nUser visibility\tLogged-in users and guest users (depending on your storefront's guest user access)\nConfigure Product Info and Options on the Product Detail Page\nPrecisely adjust which information and options are prominently available when a buyer visits the Product Detail page. Select which content is most meaningful for your buyers: short description, SKU, Add to Cart button, and so on. Show that content at the top of the page and help buyers make quick purchase decisions.\nGuidelines for Creating Page Sections\nTo show more product data on the Product Detail page—product specifications, related products, documentation, and so on—create CC Page Section records. You can define how buyers experience your added product content by specifying which content to show and where to show it.\nShow a Product's Long Description on the Product Detail Page\nA product's short description is limited to 2,000 characters. What if you have a more detailed description that you want to show on the Product Detail page? You can create a page section that shows a product's long description, which supports up to 5,000 characters.\nShow Related Products on the Product Detail Page\nAfter you create relationships between products, you can make those relationships visible for a buyer viewing the Product Detail page.\nShow Product Specs on the Product Detail Page\nHelp buyers determine whether a specific product satisfies their purchasing criteria. When you create physical, operational, or performance specifications for a product, you can easily include those specifications on the Product Detail page.\nMake Documentation Available on the Product Detail Page\nIf you've added supporting documentation for a product, you can make that documentation available directly to buyers on your storefront. Build trust with your buyers and give them confidence that they're purchasing the right product.\nShow Custom Document Types on the Product Detail Page\nIf you prefer custom product documentation types instead of the default values—such as Datasheets or Safety Documents—you can show those types on your storefront. Modify field definitions and dependencies for the CC Page Section and CC Product Media objects, and create records with your custom values.\nShow Shipping Information on the Product Detail Page\nOptionally include a product's specified shipping information such as weight, hazardous warning, or overnight availability on the Product Detail page. Create a page section that shows the shipping details in a tab or widget.\nShow Custom Content on the Product Detail Page\nEasily add your organization's custom rich text-formatted product content as a tab or widget on the Product Detail page. For example, maybe you want to highlight a product's ethical or sustainable sourcing practices, or you want to provide recommendations for recycling. Create a product tab record, and then create a page section that references the product tab's content.\nDID THIS ARTICLE SOLVE YOUR ISSUE?\nLet us know so we can improve!\nYes\nNo\n ",
